prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the Neon Type Photo Scribble Poster visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules:
- Composition: edge-to-edge toxic neon green poster field, huge black ultra-condensed all-caps words cropped by the canvas edges, one centered rectangular documentary photo block pasted over the type, one large white aerosol handwriting layer crossing the lower middle of the photo and headline.
- Typography: blunt event-flyer typography, black heavy condensed grotesk headline, tight all-caps metadata along the top and bottom margins, handwritten overlay made from thick white spray-marker strokes with soft overspray and small drips.
- Color: neon green is the dominant field, black is used for all large type, white is used only for the handwritten gesture, and realistic photo color appears only inside the central photo rectangle.
- Photography: central photo should look like candid live-event photography, eye-level or slightly low, gritty daylight or flash contrast, visible bystanders or environmental clutter, subject cropped large and immediate.
- Graphic elements: keep a flat poster base, hard rectangular photo edges, no decorative frame, no gradients, no UI, no logo marks, no platform marks.

Important content rule: preserve the visual style first, then change the source content. Use the new subject, action, prop, location, background details, and text supplied above. Do not recreate the source content listed above.
